	<div class="balanced-diet-section">
		<div class="balanced-diet diet">
			<h4>A BALANCED DIET</h4>
			<p>Protein is integral to our daily menus as they are the building blocks of life. We need protein in our diet to help repair cells and regenerate new ones. We all require a certain amount of protein to maintain good health, whether in the form of animal or plant protein. Animal proteins include meats, fish and eggs, whilst plant sources include soy, beans, legumes, nut butters and pseudocereals.
			<br></br>
			Fat is essential to human wellbeing, it provides energy and makes you feel full. Our bodies require both saturated and unsaturated fats in order to absorb vitamins A, D, E and K.  We make sure to include both types in our meals: saturated fat, mostly found in animal foods and unsaturated, mostly found in plant foods. The amount of fat required in our client's diet will be calculated and reflected in all meals. 
			<br></br>
			Complex carbohydrates do an excellent job of keeping you full and are less fattening because they take longer for our bodies to metabolise than simple carbohydrates. Most of the carbohydrates in our meals derive from green and root vegetables, plenty of seeds, pseudocereals and grains. Using this knowledge and carefully calculated portions, we create meals which aid your body in regulating its blood sugar levels. 
			</p>
		</div>
		<%= image_tag "https://res.cloudinary.com/depgwjsnd/image/upload/v1557933512/About_-_Balanced_Diet_q1wwcj.jpg", class: "diet-image" %>
	</div>

